{
    "_id": "1234567890",
    "user": ObjectId("1234567890"),
    "products": [
        {
            "product": ObjectId("1234567890"),
            "quantity": 1,
            "price": 100
        }
    ],
    "totalAmount": 100,
    "createdAt": "2025-11-28",
    "updatedAt": "2025-11-28"
}


READ SCENARIOS
1.  Get User's Cart
    Fetch cart for a specific user
    Lookup Key : user
    API : GET /cart?user_id={userId}
    DB Query : findOne({ user: <> })
    Read heavy


WRITE SCENARIOS
    1.  Add Item to Cart
        Add new product or increment quantity if exists
        API : POST /cart/add
        Write heavy
    
    2.  Remove Item from Cart
        Remove specific product from cart
        API : DELETE /cart/item
        Write heavy
    
    3.  Update Item Quantity
        Update quantity of existing cart item
        API : PUT /cart/item
        Write heavy
    
    4.  Clear Cart
        Remove all items from cart
        API : DELETE /cart
        Write heavy


INDEX
db.cart.createIndex({ user: 1 }) // For user cart lookup (most important - unique)
db.cart.createIndex({ user: 1, "products.product": 1 }) // For checking if product in cart